Files and directory management

ls------->list of directories
ls -l -------->list with details
ls -la------->list all the things in the directory
ls -ltr----->list the files in the order
ls -ltra------->list the fils in order
ls -h ------->hden files
  Cd-- ----->change current directory
pwd -------->present working directory
mkdir------->create a directory
rmdir------>remove directory
touch------>create file
cp --- copy the files or directories
mv ------->move the files one folder to another folder
vim------->edit the file contect or create a file 
:wq!------>SAVE the file
cat------>view file or read the file
less------>view file contect interactively
less filename
head------->shows first few lines
head -n 5 filename------>fist five lines
tail------>shows last few lines
tail -n 5 filename------->shows last five lines
more------>vew file content page-by-page
more filename
find ------->search files and directories
basic syntax------>find [path] [options] [expression]
  find all files in current directory----> find .
  find by name----find /home -name "sample.html"
  find by extention---find . -name "*.txt"----->-find all .txt files in current directory and subfolder
find case-insensitive------->find . -iname "sample.html"
find only directories------>find . -type d -name "text"
find only names-------> find . -type f -name ".log"
find by size ------->find /var -size +100M
find by modified time(modified in last one day)----->find . -mtime -1
  Modified in last 7 days ago ----->find . -mtime +7
Find empty files and directoris------> find . -empty
find and delete ------->find . -name "*.tmp" -type f -delete
find and execute a command------>find . -name "*.log" -exec ls -lh {} \;
Locate------->locate filename





  
